The Presidential residence of Cheong Wa Dae opened its gate wide to welcome the return of Korean athletes from the 2010 Vancouver Winter Olympics. At the luncheon party that took place Wednesday (Mar. 3) President Lee Myung-bak invited not only athletes and coaches but also sports officials, including the head of the Korean Olympic Committee Park Yong-sung and IOC member Lee Kun-hee, making over 120 guests for the occasion.
